Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.14,0:00:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate that you fixed me\Na box lunch for a change, but, Sis,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.61,0:00:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why ethnic?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.07,0:00:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.24,0:00:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.41,0:00:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for minding the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.37,0:00:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.41,0:00:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.12,0:00:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won, we won!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.04,0:00:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went down to the wire, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.50,0:00:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations on your victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.42,0:00:25.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.21,0:00:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much. It was all\Nthanks to your help, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.34,0:00:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah... Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I was shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.93,0:00:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, you would have been\Nthe last person on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.72,0:00:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I'd expect to do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.97,0:00:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just caught up in the\Nfestival mood. I won't do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.35,0:00:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there is something I'd like you to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.94,0:00:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.49,0:00:59.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Cooking Club has already\Nlost its ladle.... Jumonji
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.97,0:01:23.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You hold your breath to make it through\Nthe bewildering day that confronts you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.81,0:01:29.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You know what this is, don't you?\NWhat do you want to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.98,0:01:36.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The pain from shrugging\Nit all off as nothing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.57,0:01:42.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}urges you on enough to be encouraging{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.49,0:01:49.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Catching hold but making a mess,\Nwe're still inadequate{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.12,0:01:57.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but as long as we can forge\Nour shining, unseen future selves...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.97,0:02:05.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Awaken and run where it takes you,\Nleaving mirages behind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.56,0:02:12.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run with your desire to change,\Nfrom your comfort zone into freedom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.15,0:02:19.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Start choosing between now\Nand the brilliance you can attain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.53,0:02:27.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unaware of your destination,\Ndeep breaths following shallow ones{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm... Your ladle was stolen, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.88,0:02:38.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Jumonji Affair
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.88,0:02:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. But only from our table.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.51,0:02:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone sure has a lot of free time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.59,0:02:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just the Cooking Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same thing has been foisted upon\Nthe Go Club and the A Capella Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.64,0:02:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Fortunetelling Club, too!\NIt had the same kind of note.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.60,0:02:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, the confession note said...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.10,0:02:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone sure has an {\i1}awful {\i0}lot of free time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, this spiciness is so good...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:02:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.65,0:03:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.99,0:03:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.32,0:03:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda Eru's curiosity\Nis about to kick in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could do something like this\Nin the middle of the culture festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.91,0:03:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are they appropriating\NJumonji-{\i1}san{\i0}'s name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.59,0:03:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are they stealing\None thing after another?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curiou...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have time to chase after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.26,0:03:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These anthologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.22,0:03:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About these anthologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.18,0:03:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even publicizing them\Nlow-key during our events,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.35,0:03:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we're going\Nto sell a whole lot of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.65,0:03:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.23,0:03:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to have to do something\Nmuch more attention-grabbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! So I was thinking:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.11,0:03:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if we pitched this phantom thievery\Nto the Wall Newspaper Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if possible, have the\Nschool radio put it over the air, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.12,0:03:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we do all that, our anthologies\Nwill be in high demand, won't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That follows.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.29,0:03:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you say "pitch it,"\Nwhat are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.67,0:03:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This incident has nothing to do\Nwith the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.80,0:04:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We do it like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.68,0:04:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Classic Lit Club's master\Ndetective, Oreki Hotaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.05,0:04:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will catch Jumonji, the phantom thief\Nupsetting the culture festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.35,0:04:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To learn more about his exploits up to now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.68,0:04:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,see the Classic Lit\NClub's anthology, {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be a fantastic way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.61,0:04:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, not bad, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.61,0:04:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right? This will unmask\NJumonji's true identity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.61,0:04:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as publicize the Classic\NLit Club... Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling a master detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.57,0:04:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no way I'm playing panda\Nto lure in customers! Hmph!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.66,0:04:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's give it a try, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.08,0:04:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even assuming I'm willing\Nto become a clown,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.50,0:04:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are 1,000 students alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if you add in all\Nthe visitors, it's even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are we going to catch anyone\Namong all those people?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.43,0:04:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it that hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.43,0:04:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.23,0:05:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only this so-called phantom thief\Ntargeted the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.65,0:05:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.11,0:05:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what if we hit ourselves?\NOverruled!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.65,0:05:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yow...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.86,0:05:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm kidding, I'm kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.66,0:05:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Target, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.49,0:05:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which clubs have been\Nstolen from so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.79,0:05:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Go Club, the A Capella Club,\Nthe Cooking Club, uh... What else?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fortunetelling Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.34,0:05:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.84,0:05:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.38,0:05:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The A Capella Club, the Go Club,\Nthe Fortunetelling Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.30,0:05:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Cooking Club, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.43,0:05:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ABC!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.89,0:05:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Suzuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.44,0:05:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clubs that go with "E" are the\NFilm Club, the Gardening Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.36,0:05:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you had anything stolen from your club?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.77,0:05:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, like a robbery.\NAnd the SF Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.44,0:05:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.44,0:05:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, never mind, then. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The regularity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.65,0:05:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's an extremely simple one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.28,0:05:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The A Capella Club;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.28,0:05:56.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,'A' Capella Club
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.16,0:05:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the {\i1}Igo {\i0}[Go] Club;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.16,0:05:56.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,'I'-go Club
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.82,0:05:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the {\i1}Uranai {\i0}[Fortunetelling] Club;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.82,0:05:56.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,'U'-ranai Club
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.28,0:05:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,skip a letter to the {\i1}Oryori {\i0}[Cooking] Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.28,0:05:56.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,'O'-ryori Club
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:56.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,'E'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if an "E" club pops up next,\Nthere's no question about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.96,0:05:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Japanese alphabetic order, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.96,0:06:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water pistol? Ah, mm-hm. Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.00,0:06:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Gardening Club has been hit.\NThey were gone for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.25,0:06:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and one of their water pistols was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.80,0:06:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water pistol?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.80,0:06:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For fire safety when\Nroasting sweet potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.22,0:06:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A customer yesterday from\Nthe Gardening Club had one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.43,0:06:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Christie's{\i1} The A.B.C. Murders{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.68,0:06:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the "A" person is killed in\Nthe "A" location, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An {\i1}otama {\i0}[ladle] was stolen from\Nthe {\i1}Oryori {\i0}[Cooking] Club...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.40,0:06:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, just a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.56,0:06:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, did you ask what was\Nstolen from the Fortunetelling Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.94,0:06:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. It was the\N"Wheel of Fortune," a tarot card.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:38.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,A Capella Club → (drink) {\i1}Igo{\i0} Club → (Go stones) {\i1}Uranai{\i0} Club →\N({\i1}Unmei no Hi{\i0}) {\i1}Engei{\i0} Club → (water pistol) {\i1}Oryori{\i0} Club → ({\i1}otama{\i0})
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.75,0:06:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Gardening Club's water pistol\Nwas an "{\i1}eikei{\i0}" [AK] wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.58,0:06:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AK? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.67,0:06:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Russian-made assault rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.38,0:06:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that counts for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.42,0:06:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then the {\i1}Igo {\i0}[Go] Club gets\N"{\i1}ishi{\i0}" [stone], doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.01,0:06:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could be. What about the A Capella Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.55,0:06:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't matter. If we look\Ninto it, we'll find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.10,0:06:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.06,0:07:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the culprit's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.19,0:07:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says "Jumonji."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.85,0:07:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why read it like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The usual reading would be "Jumoji," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.53,0:07:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"{\i1}Jumoji{\i0}" [tenth letter]!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.78,0:07:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! A-I-U-E-O, Ka-Ki-Ku-Ke-Ko,\Nup to the tenth letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.82,0:07:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the last letter will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.53,0:07:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ko"! The {\i1}Koten {\i0}[Classic Lit] Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.58,0:07:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think this is enough of\Na pitch for the Classic Lit Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.04,0:07:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go discuss this with the\NWall Newspaper Club right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's pretty excited about this, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.88,0:07:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.67,0:07:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Oh... I just thought of\Nsomething. This whole thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, never mind. I'm going\Nto go check something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.06,0:07:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.69,0:07:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.15,0:07:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara, aren't you going\Nback to the Manga Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.32,0:07:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Is there something\Nwrong with me being here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.37,0:08:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:05.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Biology Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.75,0:08:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The trick to negotiating...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.34,0:08:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, look as though you expect\Nsomething of the other person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, downplay your benefit from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.51,0:08:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Third, ask someone of the\Nopposite sex, away from public view.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish! I'll go interview\Nthe Gardening Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what about the A Capella Club?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.32,0:08:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling them now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.70,0:08:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, hurry it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.70,0:08:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Cooking Club! We're looking\Ninto it now. Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Tomita? I need to ask you something...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times\Ndo I have to tell you?! If you have time to chat, move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.20,0:08:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me... Excuse me...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about this, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nbut we're a little busy right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.54,0:08:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you come by again later sometime?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.29,0:08:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. Well, another time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.75,0:08:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't going to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.09,0:08:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is about the Classic Lit Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.30,0:08:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's that again, you need to\Nhave a special angle or else...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.01,0:08:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we {\i1}do {\i0}have an angle!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.64,0:08:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.64,0:09:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're a little short on time.\NCould you make this brief...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, hey! Where do you think\Nyou're taking me? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is something I can only discuss\Nwith the Wall Newspaper Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.95,0:09:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is to say, um, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.95,0:09:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,am pinning my hopes on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.83,0:09:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You are? Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.54,0:09:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's not much in it\Nfor the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.88,0:09:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? Isn't this\Nsomething you'd like to get behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.14,0:09:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.05,0:09:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.14,0:09:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.27,0:09:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, we're busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.94,0:09:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't have a story,\NI'll talk to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.69,0:09:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the story! There is someone\Nat the culture festival
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.74,0:09:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who is stealing things\Nfrom different clubs!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.53,0:09:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.33,0:10:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jumonji!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.33,0:10:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're talking about Jumonji, right?!\NDo you know something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.04,0:10:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Um, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.75,0:10:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Japanese alphabetical order.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Fortunetelling Club was hit,\Ntoo, you say? So that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.97,0:10:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is the {\i1}Kabe {\i0}[Wall]\NNewspaper Club, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.64,0:10:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Then you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.72,0:10:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They got our {\i1}katta {\i0}[cutter] knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.85,0:10:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the reason why\Nyou're so busy right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.81,0:10:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I do hate that it happened to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but we've been waiting\Nfor a story like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to admit, though, I'm\Nimpressed that you picked up on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. Oreki-{\i1}san {\i0}did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.66,0:10:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... You don't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, thanks. You've been helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Togaito-{\i1}san{\i0}, please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.04,0:10:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already told you as much as I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.63,0:10:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so please be sure to write\Nabout the Classic Lit Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:11:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right? Please?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.43,0:11:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Belaboring the point there was\Nthe same as doubting Togaito-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.57,0:11:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.57,0:11:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Excuse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}! Well? Did\Nyou get any results?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.99,0:11:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.37,0:11:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, inside joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Ah, more importantly, I\Nheard from the A Capella Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.54,0:11:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was apple juice that was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.67,0:11:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also heard from the\NWall Newspaper Club
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.05,0:11:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that they had their cutter knife stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.80,0:11:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That covers "Ka." It's Japanese\Nalphabetical order for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.55,0:11:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that the next one, "Ki,"\Ncan only be the {\i1}Kijutsu {\i0}[Magic] Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.76,0:11:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost time for the\NMagic Club's next performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we keep our eyes peeled...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.39,0:11:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can catch them in the act?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.48,0:11:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.52,0:11:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's this kind of phantom\Nthief's Achilles' heel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:11:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's bound by his own rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.07,0:12:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be hard to uncover\Nwho "Jumoji" is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.37,0:12:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if we find him out at "Ki"...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.95,0:12:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit won't ever reach\Nthe Classic Lit Club, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.00,0:12:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are any number\Nof ways to deal with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.67,0:12:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe so, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.67,0:12:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I'll stake out the\NMagic Club. No time like the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.01,0:12:26.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shuubun{\i0} ('Middle of Autumn')\NWhen light\Nfindeth equal measure with darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.18,0:12:26.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.01,0:12:29.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Program\N5. 'Close-up Card Magic'\N1st-years Takamura Yoichi / Nagai Kaori
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.26,0:12:30.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,5th Performance: 14:30
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.15,0:12:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still only 2:00, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.11,0:12:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, if it isn't Fukube.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.32,0:12:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tani-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.32,0:12:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here, then it means\Nyou must know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.41,0:12:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.20,0:12:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb! About the\Nphantom thief Jumoji!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.00,0:12:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha, ha! Then this will be\Nour next competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.25,0:13:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know about the\NWall Newspaper Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cutter knife, right? Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.05,0:13:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the Wall Newspaper Club\Nhas joined in on the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next issue's top story is on Jumoji.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.05,0:13:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, they apparently\Nplan to run an extra
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.39,0:13:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,covering exclusively any group\Nthat catches the phantom thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.27,0:13:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.35,0:13:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I hate to say it, but\NI'm going to win this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appearances to the contrary,\NI'm actually quite the mystery fan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.07,0:13:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go easy on me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.57,0:13:27.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.45,0:13:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara, you've\Nread Christie's {\i1}The A.B.C. Murders{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.41,0:13:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.83,0:13:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I have a question for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.46,0:13:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there a reason why the\Nkillings were in ABC order?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.38,0:13:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spoiler alert. Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.42,0:13:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"He wanted to kill in ABC order,\Nso that's what he tried."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.97,0:13:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that would make a good story?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.18,0:13:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.01,0:13:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you thinking that this\Nmatter is the same way?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.60,0:13:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.14,0:14:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In time, anyone could have figured out\Nthe Japanese alphabetic order rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.40,0:14:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's something "Jumoji"\Nmust have expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, that's true enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.36,0:14:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking there's a possibility\Nof some hidden purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.74,0:14:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or meaning in the way\Nthings are being stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is, if it's not just some\Ncrime for the fun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.41,0:14:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki, do you want to\Ncatch this "Jumoji" now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who, me? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.84,0:14:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.51,0:14:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But once Chitanda says she's curious,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.64,0:14:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it becomes an issue that\Nultimately can't be avoided.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could ignore her, couldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.72,0:14:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not someone I can just ignore,\Nwhich is why it's a hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.81,0:14:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How silly. Okay then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.19,0:14:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. Oh, come to think\Nof it, thanks for the flour.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.24,0:14:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.74,0:14:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.12,0:14:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you asking for money?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.33,0:14:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make it sound sordid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.12,0:15:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got that flour through\Nthe Warashibe Protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.79,0:15:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.67,0:15:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me something in return.\NOr you could just break the protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.09,0:15:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it. Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.14,0:15:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.93,0:15:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.06,0:15:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.52,0:15:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But without that you can't cosplay...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.81,0:15:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call it cosplay, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.86,0:15:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Club's 5th performance\Nwill be starting shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:36.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Club
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.29,0:15:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-{\i1}senpai{\i0}, hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.88,0:15:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.92,0:15:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like magic tricks?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.26,0:15:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know them well enough\Nto say I like them. Is that weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:15:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? No. Just a bit surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.52,0:16:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could she be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.52,0:16:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, he didn't have\Nto say it like that, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.19,0:16:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Mayaka's Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.86,0:16:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.15,0:16:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her at the Manga Club yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.45,0:16:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This looks entertaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.78,0:16:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.24,0:16:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mune, don't go deciding this yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's Tanabe-{\i1}senpai {\i0}and... Ten-hut!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.04,0:16:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, don't get mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Student Council President Kugayama Muneyoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.33,0:16:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Miss Empress.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.92,0:16:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.63,0:16:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.59,0:16:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Hey, Fukube.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.59,0:16:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.93,0:16:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting! The Magic Club's\Nperformance will now begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.93,0:16:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much for\Ncoming together here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.85,0:16:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please enjoy watching the tricks\Nthat we in the Magic Club
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.52,0:16:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have been practicing daily to master.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.23,0:16:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.44,0:16:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this many people watching,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how are you going to commit your theft,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.62,0:16:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,phantom thief "Jumoji"?\NAll right, first off,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.33,0:17:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takamura Yoichi will\Nperform "Living Dead"...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.95,0:17:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.54,0:17:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.50,0:17:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"{\i1}Kyandaru{\i0}" [candle]!\NGet a spare...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.76,0:17:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.51,0:17:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"When" nothing. Nobody but the\Nperformers went near the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.56,0:17:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it was taken\Nbefore they started.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.27,0:17:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh, why did I even\Ncome here, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.49,0:17:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it,\Nthere's no evidence to show
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.53,0:17:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Jumoji steals\Nduring a performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:46.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the Manga Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.58,0:17:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.00,0:17:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we selling more than we did yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.04,0:17:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, we are. Maybe the\Nposters are having an effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.26,0:17:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should have just done as\NSenpai said, shouldn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.47,0:18:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. If a certain someone\Nhadn't objected,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.47,0:18:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we could have sold even more yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, it's so sad\Nto say it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.35,0:18:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason to mind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.02,0:18:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.81,0:18:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that business about\Nnot being able to find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.48,0:18:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a lie, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.94,0:18:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet she actually got\Nscared all of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.99,0:18:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about the manga she was going\Nto show off not being that great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.20,0:18:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bringing up a {\i1}doujinshi\N{\i0}nobody's heard of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just to try to look like\Na know-it-all, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.87,0:18:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's her, that's her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.21,0:18:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet that manga\Ndoesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, hold on...\NStop! That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.04,0:18:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you've never heard\Nof it, then keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.76,0:18:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.30,0:18:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But, Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.68,0:18:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.26,0:18:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said if you don't know it,\Nthen keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.81,0:18:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, President, how\Nwas the Magic Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm, it was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.06,0:18:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? Maybe I'll go\Nand see it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, go right on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.86,0:18:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What time does it start again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.53,0:19:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They do it several times per day,\Nso I think you'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.58,0:19:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.24,0:19:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I need to\Nstep out for a bit, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.10,0:19:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fu...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.56,0:19:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so pathetic, huh? I want to go\Nrunning to Fuku-{\i1}chan {\i0}and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.40,0:19:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.36,0:19:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, Yuasa-{\i1}senpai{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.36,0:19:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry things have\Ngotten so awkward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.95,0:19:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are {\i1}you {\i0}apologizing, Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.20,0:19:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For not saying anything sooner.\NI wanted to take your side, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you did that, there'd be friction\Nbetween you and Kochi-{\i1}senpai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.84,0:20:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't want that to happen.\NI think it's better this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.26,0:20:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako doesn't really mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.35,0:20:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.10,0:20:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean Kochi. Kochi Ayako.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.97,0:20:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know she\Ndoesn't really mean it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.56,0:20:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Ayako and I are friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.69,0:20:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako and Haruna were friends, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.45,0:20:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haruna? Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anjo Haruna. One of the authors\Nof {\i1}A Corpse By Evening{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.83,0:20:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a collaborative work?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.92,0:20:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone else was the artist.\NAyako would probably know who.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What year and what class is she in?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.38,0:20:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Haruna isn't around anymore.\NShe transferred away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.76,0:20:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.43,0:20:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But just because Kochi-{\i1}senpai\N{\i0}was friends with Anjo Haruna-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how can you be sure that\Nshe doesn't really mean it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.36,0:21:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, that's a good question.\NI'm sorry, but I can't say any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.24,0:21:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, Ayako is my friend after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.33,0:21:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then explaining why would make\Nyou speak ill of Kochi-{\i1}senpai{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.33,0:21:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I cool off a bit,\NI'll come back inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.13,0:21:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.75,0:21:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right back in, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Extra! Extra!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.68,0:21:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Must-read!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.69,0:21:40.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Secret Exploits of the\NPhantom Thief Jumoji
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.15,0:21:45.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, ah, the nerve of this rascal! He even went so far\Nas to take a cutter knife from the Wall Newspaper Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.36,0:21:48.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a clear and unambiguous challenge to the news\Nmedia. A way must be found to stop Jumoji's thievery...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.91,0:21:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all the information we have at present. As such, gentle reader,\Nit can be supposed that Jumoji's final misdeed will take place
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.62,0:21:53.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,on the third day between noon and 2:00, with either\Nthe 'Classic Lit Club' or the 'Industrial Arts Club.'
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.37,0:21:54.66,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Classic Lit Club
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.96,0:21:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Togaito-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.59,0:22:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been had, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.80,0:22:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A candle was stolen from the Magic Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.72,0:22:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They even found a confession note.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.01,0:22:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want Jumoji caught before\Nhe gets to the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.93,0:22:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.27,0:22:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I could catch\Nhim in the act, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.73,0:22:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That the theft would happen\Nduring the performance?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.23,0:22:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.28,0:22:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jumoji didn't reveal anything about\Nthe exact time of the crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.74,0:22:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was true of the\NCooking Club's ladle, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.45,0:22:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you realized that, why\Ndidn't you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.75,0:22:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know you were trying\Nto catch him in the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.04,0:22:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.63,0:22:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.67,0:22:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-{\i1}san {\i0}said that the 20 volumes\Nof {\i1}Hyouka {\i0}that we gave to her
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.63,0:22:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are selling at a favorable pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.89,0:22:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's just how Irisu works.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.01,0:22:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one other thing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.81,0:22:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the Wall Newspaper's 4:00 edition
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.73,0:23:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a story that\Ncovers the "Jumoji" case.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.90,0:23:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It even covers the Japanese\Nalphabetical order rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.98,0:23:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.07,0:23:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Classic Lit Club's name also appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.40,0:23:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It said that Jumoji's last crime would\Nbe against the Classic Lit Club
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.49,0:23:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the Industrial Arts Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.95,0:23:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Industrial Arts Club? We have one of those?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.62,0:23:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we do, now that I think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.62,0:23:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they get hit, our whole\Nplan goes up in smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.75,0:23:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking of making a deal with\Nthe Broadcasting Club tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.34,0:23:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can get them to\Ncover the Classic Lit Club
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.25,0:23:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on their schoolwide broadcast...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.05,0:23:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.93,0:23:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you look exhaust...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.26,0:23:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to keep at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.05,0:23:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.76,0:23:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How were our sales today?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.98,0:23:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not counting the ones we\Ngave to Irisu, we sold 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.73,0:23:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remarkable, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.40,0:23:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remarkable? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.61,0:23:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.74,0:23:51.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Remaining: 137
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.54,0:24:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It {\i1}is {\i0}on me to go around\Nmaking requests...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.09,0:24:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but somehow, I feel so tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.05,0:24:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Body Talk{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.51,0:24:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a step below {\i1}A Corpse By Evening{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.85,0:24:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's still pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.49,0:24:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh. My stuff is a hundred steps below.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.62,0:24:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro has changed. Or rather,\Nhe's exhibiting his true worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.58,0:24:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All because of meeting Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.13,0:24:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's someone who holds that sense\Nof unpredictability that I love so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.92,0:24:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that something that I can look at\Nand just think, "That's nice"?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.60,0:24:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are over 1,000 suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.64,0:25:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one could possibly be led to\Nthe culprit by simple deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.19,0:25:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that catching them\Nin the act is the best we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.57,0:25:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro really isn't cut out\Nfor a case like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.70,0:25:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll solve it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.41,0:25:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, I'm going to catch\NJumoji, just you watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.00,0:25:24.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the Kanyasai Homepage
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.75,0:25:26.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Mail order
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.96,0:25:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, they do mail order, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.80,0:25:58.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This situation is an unscientific\Nmontage of emotions{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.48,0:26:02.14,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who is calling whom?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.14,0:26:08.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your gaze darts away when I turn around\N(I can feel it){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.11,0:26:10.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's unkind to tell me I'm imagining things{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.36,0:26:15.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They say having antennas\Nis a talent, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.90,0:26:20.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean I want to know\N(I mean) (don't you?){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.99,0:26:27.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll turn up the heat on your youth\Nfor you now, while there's time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.77,0:26:32.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we can solve this tomorrow,\Nwhy not solve it right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.45,0:26:38.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to solve your mystery{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.01,0:26:42.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Track down that secretive boyish figure!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.73,0:26:50.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Today) you are a fantasy,\Ndrawing me to you, no fair!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.28,0:26:55.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My curiosity is expanding,\Nlack of tricks notwithstanding{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.94,0:27:02.85,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm fascinated, and I have to know, why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.83,0:27:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "The Final Target."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.69,0:27:13.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Final Target
